# Fixing SectionEditor Nested Array Bug

I identified a bug in [AdminPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%82%B0%EB%8F%8C%EA%B5%90%ED%9A%8C%20%ED%99%88%ED%8E%98%EC%9D%B4%EC%A7%80/src/pages/AdminPage.jsx)'s [SectionEditor](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%82%B0%EB%8F%8C%EA%B5%90%ED%9A%8C%20%ED%99%88%ED%8E%98%EC%9D%B4%EC%A7%80/src/pages/AdminPage.jsx#5-141) component. When editing an "Array of Strings" that is nested inside another object (e.g., `parish.groups[i].items`), the update logic incorrectly targets the top-level section object instead of the nested object, leading to data corruption.

Although the user reported this as a "Footer reverting" issue, creating malformed data structures can lead to unpredictable behavior during saves. I will fix this specific bug to ensure data integrity.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> This fix addresses a specific bug in how certain complex data fields (like Parish groups) are saved. This should improve the overall reliability of the Admin Page.

## Proposed Changes

### Component Layer
#### [MODIFY] [AdminPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/산돌교회 홈페이지/src/pages/AdminPage.jsx)
- Update [SectionEditor](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%82%B0%EB%8F%8C%EA%B5%90%ED%9A%8C%20%ED%99%88%ED%8E%98%EC%9D%B4%EC%A7%80/src/pages/AdminPage.jsx#5-141)'s [renderInput](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%82%B0%EB%8F%8C%EA%B5%90%ED%9A%8C%20%ED%99%88%ED%8E%98%EC%9D%B4%EC%A7%80/src/pages/AdminPage.jsx#31-80) function.
- In the "Array of Strings" handling block (lines 53+), modify the `onChange` handler.
- If `parentKey` and `index` are present (indicating nesting), use [handleChange](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%82%B0%EB%8F%8C%EA%B5%90%ED%9A%8C%20%ED%99%88%ED%8E%98%EC%9D%B4%EC%A7%80/src/pages/AdminPage.jsx#8-30) logic (or replicate it) to update the specific nested item, rather than merging into the root `data`.

